Azure Cost Management and Billing helps organizations monitor, control, and optimize cloud spending.

Core capabilities include:

* Budget creation
* Cost analysis dashboards
* Spending forecasts
* Cost alerts
* Billing reports

For example, an organization can set monthly budgets for each department and receive alerts when spending approaches limits.

# Real-Life Use Case:
A real-life use case is startups preventing budget overruns while scaling cloud infrastructure.

# Real-Life Example:
Another example is enterprises allocating cloud costs across business units.

Cost Management improves financial visibility and supports strategic resource planning.
